  "category": "ePOS User Manual",
  "content": "<div class=\"ql-editor read-mode\"><p><a href=\"#_Toc139272808\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">I. Getting Start</a></p><p><a href=\"#_Toc139272809\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">i.</a> <a href=\"#_Toc139272809\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Start Application</a></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: white; color: rgb(66, 66, 66);\">For Desktop:</strong><span style=\"background-color: white; color: rgb(66, 66, 66);\"> You can start </span><strong style=\"background-color: white; color: rgb(66, 66, 66);\">ePOS</strong><span style=\"background-color: white; color: rgb(66, 66, 66);\"> system by double click or right click on shortcut icon&nbsp;on your computer desktop (</span><em style=\"background-color: white; color: rgb(66, 66, 66);\">if you right click on icon then click Open</em><span style=\"background-color: white; color: rgb(66, 66, 66);\">).</span></p><p><img src=\"/files/5ZNMl3Q.png\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto;\" align=\"center\"></p><p><strong style=\"background-color: white; color: rgb(66, 66, 66);\">For Mobile:</strong><span style=\"background-color: white; color: rgb(66, 66, 66);\"> You can start </span><strong style=\"background-color: white; color: rgb(66, 66, 66);\">ePOS Mobile</strong><span style=\"background-color: white; color: rgb(66, 66, 66);\"> system by tab on shortcut icon&nbsp;&nbsp;on your mobile screen.</span></p><p><img src=\"/files/5GtiQGn.png\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto;\" align=\"center\"></p><p><a href=\"#_Toc139272810\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ii.</a> <a href=\"#_Toc139272810\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">How to Login, Logout and Exit System?</a></p><ol><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span>&nbsp;Login</li></ol><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">For Desktop: </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">&nbsp;After you double click or right click the shortcut icon on desktop to start system then you’ll see </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">Login screen.</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\"> So, you need to enter your </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">PIN Code </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">then press </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">Login </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">button for login to use system.</span></p><p><img src=\"/files/ZS6FNMK.png\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto;\" align=\"center\"></p><p><span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">If your success on login system, you’ll see system </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">Dashboard</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\"> as show in below.</span></p><p><img src=\"/files/rJM4MGk.png\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto;\" align=\"center\"></p><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">For Mobile: </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">&nbsp;After you tab icon on your mobile screen to start system then you’ll see </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">Login screen.</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\"> So you need to enter your </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">PIN Code </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">then press </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">Login </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">button for login to use system. So you need to enter your </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">PIN Code </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">then tab </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">Login </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">button for login to use system. If your success on login system, you’ll see system </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">Dashboard</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\"> as show in right of login screen.</span></p><p><img src=\"/files/fExLFzj.png\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto;\" align=\"center\"></p><ol><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span>&nbsp;Logout</li></ol><p><span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">When you stand on </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">dashboard </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">screen, you’ve two ways for logout system.</span></p><p>&nbsp;-\t<span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">You’ll see button </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">Logout</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\"> then you can click or press on the button to logout.</span></p><p>&nbsp;-\t<span style=\"color: rgb(66, 66, 66); background-color: white;\">On system app-bar of top-left you’ll see Profile&nbsp;then click or press on it and menu will show, after that you find logout button at end-of-menu so can click or press it to logout.</span></p><p><img src=\"/files/Utr5Ewp.png\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto;\" align=\"center\"></p><p><img src=\"/files/LHbvOP5.png\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto;\" align=\"center\"></p><p><img src=\"/files/AQ4QmWA.png\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto;\" align=\"center\"></p><ol><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span>\tExit (Desktop)</li></ol><p><span style=\"background-color: white; color: rgb(66, 66, 66);\">If you stand on </span><strong style=\"background-color: white; color: rgb(66, 66, 66);\">login screen</strong><span style=\"background-color: white; color: rgb(66, 66, 66);\">, you will see exit and if you press it will log you out of application.</span></p><p><img src=\"/files/lJ4b0TT.png\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto;\" align=\"center\"></p><p><a href=\"#_Toc139272811\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">iii.</a> <a href=\"#_Toc139272811\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">ePOS Overview</a></p><p><span style=\"background-color: white; color: rgb(66, 66, 66);\">When your success on login system, you’ll see the information of your current branch, outlet, station’s name. And the below of system information are system features.</span></p><p><img src=\"/files/dxLXcel.png\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto;\" align=\"center\"></p><ol><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>Start Working Day : </strong>Before you start making order, you’ve to do process <strong>Start Working Day</strong>. Once you’ve working day opened, this button will change to <strong>Close Working Day</strong>.</li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>Close Working Day : </strong>This option will be appearing after you opened <strong>Working Day</strong>. We use this option to close current working and print out of day-end report. It’s very useful when you have multiple cashier shift per day.</li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>Start Cashier Shift : </strong>Use this option to open <strong>Cashier Shift</strong>. It’ll manage all sale transactions with your current working staffs and it’ll separate report between each shift.</li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>Close Cashier Shift : </strong>Just like working day. It’ll appear after your shift is opened. We do this operation when your current shift end before next shift start. In order to <strong>Close Working Day, </strong>we’ve to close all <strong>Cashier Shift.</strong></li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>POS : </strong>It stands for <strong>POINT OF SALE</strong>. Also it is the main module of ePOS system. We’re use it to making order.</li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>Pending Order : </strong>This option we’re use to manage the bill aren’t payment yet.</li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>Receipt List : </strong>All of your invoices was closed or settled payment or paid receipts are in here. Also you can find your old bills and do some actions such as view detail bill, re-print, adjust or modify your current closed bills.</li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>Customer : </strong>ePOS also have feature to manage your customer information. If you wish to track order of tour customer, you can enter customer information here.</li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>Cash Drawer</strong> : This option we’re use to manage cash-float such as starting amount, cash drop in, cash expense or deposit to accountant or owner.</li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>Open Cash Drawer : </strong>The button Open Cash Drawer is a small feature, but also it important and easy use for open drawer box without key unlock.</li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>Report : </strong>For frontend of ePOS system have cashier reports only. We provide best summary report for your business shift-end report and day-end report.</li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>Customer Display</strong>&nbsp;: Absolutely a slide view of second screen ePOS.</li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>Wi-Fi : </strong>It very little, simple feature but it’ll be useful if you want to print out password Wi-Fi slip or show Wi-Fi password to your customer on <strong>waiting receipt</strong>.</li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>Logout : </strong>When you click or press on this button your account logged on will be logout from system. We recommend you to logout from ePOS system when away from your desk to prevent some unusual activities.</li></ol><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>ePOS home screen after Working Day and Cashier Shift was started</strong></p><p><img src=\"/files/QDPrRp3.png\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto;\" align=\"center\"></p><p><br></p></div>",
